GLM ANALYSIS

This folder contains files and scripts to run the GLM analysis for the multisensory scenes in MTL study.
The code can be used to perform 2 sets of analyses:

1. Subject-level analysis of univariate responses per ROI for experimental conditions.
2. Across-subject whole-brain statistical maps in MNI space for defined contrasts.

The following scripts should be run in the following order to complete this analysis.

1. glm_contrasts.py

This script performs the following:
- Loads in all the BOLD data, labels, and confounds
- Creates design matrices for Audio, Visual, Congruent, and Incongruent conditions
- Fits a first-level GLM model per subject and saves:
    - Basic maps for each condition in T1w space
    - User defined contrasts in T1w space and MNI space

All parameters to run this script are defined inside the python file. The following bash command submits to the cluster:

sbatch run_glm_contrasts_PP.sh <net-ID>
Eg. sbatch run_glm_contrasts_PP.sh or62

2. run_randomise_glm.sh

This script performs the following:
- Creates a merged 4D file using FSL merge from each subject's contrast file
- Runs a one-tailed t-test with 5000 permutations using FSL randomise & returns corrected & uncorrected p-value maps

The following call is used on the terminal:
sbatch run_randomise_glm.sh <net-ID> <contrast>
Eg. sbatch run_randomise_glm.sh or62 visual-audio

3. glm_beta_analysis.py

This scripts performs the following:
- Loop over all subjects, conditions, and ROIs
- Load in the condition level betas in T1w space
- Mask the betas using the appropriate resamples mask (ASHS/HarOxf)
- Average the betas for the ROI and store it in a CSV

The following call is used on the terminal:
sbatch run_glm_beta_analysis.sh <net-ID>
Eg. sbatch run_glm_beta_analysis_PP.sh or62

